# Security & Protections

## Baseline
- Validate all input; reject unknown fields.
- Sanitize payloads to prevent injection.
- Apply rate limits on public endpoints.
- Use secure headers and CORS allowlist.
- Store secrets in env, never in code.

## Auth
- Use access tokens with short TTL.
- Hash passwords with `bcrypt`.
- Enforce authorization at middleware or controller boundary.

## Logging
- Structured logs only; never log secrets/PII.
- Add request id and user id (when present).

## Base Packages
- Runtime: `express`, `cors`, `helmet`, `dotenv`.
- Security: `express-rate-limit`, `hpp`, `express-mongo-sanitize` (as needed).
- Validation: `zod` or `joi`.
- Logging: `pino`, `pino-http`.
- Auth: `jsonwebtoken`, `bcrypt`.
